                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/243.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-22T21:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 22, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Government candidate Obregón was elected president of Congress to-day by 30
                    majority out of 178.</p>
                <p>Representatives of many American mining companies have called at Embassy to-day
                    to advise me that the prohibition of the importation of dynamite will soon cause
                    the shutting down of all mines and the discharge of some 20,000 employees, who
                    will immediately join the forces of disorder.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
